org.openbel.framework.core.kamstore.model
Class KamBuilder

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.core.kamstore.model.KamBuilder

public class KamBuilder
extends Object

KamBuilder defines a builder object used to assemble a Kam. The builder allows for:

  • adding existing (already kam-bound) Kam.KamNode and Kam.KamEdge objects
  • creating new (not backed by kam) Kam.KamNode and Kam.KamEdge objects
  • remove existing Kam.KamNode and Kam.KamEdge objects

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

Constructor Detail

KamBuilder

public KamBuilder(KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo kamInfo)
Construct from the provided kamInfo object to maintain a reference to the source Kam.

The source kam reference is used to construct the builder's Kam. References back to the KamStore data (i.e. supporting terms and evidence) are not supported with this constructor.

Parameters:
kamInfo - KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo, the reference to the source Kam

KamBuilder

public KamBuilder(Kam kam)
Construct with the structure from the provided KAM.

The topology from the sourceKam is built into the builder's kam instance. The kam node and kam edge ids are preserved to provide reference back to the KamStore data (i.e supporting terms and evidence).

Parameters:
kam - KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo the source kam, which cannot be null
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if sourceKam, nodes, or edges is null

public Kam.KamNode addExistingNode(Kam.KamNode kamNode)
Adds an existing Kam.KamNode previously associated with the source kam. The kam node will maintain its node id which allows its associated data to be retrieved from the resulting kam.

addExistingEdge

public Kam.KamEdge addExistingEdge(Integer edgeId,
                                   Kam.KamNode sourceNode,
                                   RelationshipType reltype,
                                   Kam.KamNode targetNode)
Adds an existing edge to the target kam. The existing edge is identified by the provided edgeId to maintain reference to the source kam's edge.

To add existing nodes for this kamEdge you must first call createNewNode. The source and target nodes must exist in the target kam in order for this new edge to be valid.

Parameters:
edgeId - Integer, the existing edge id in the source kam, which cannot be null
sourceNode - Kam.KamNode, the source node from the target kam, which cannot be null
reltype - RelationshipType, the existing edge relationship, which cannot be null
targetNode - Kam.KamNode, the target node from the target kam, which cannot be null
Returns:
the created edge in the target
Throws:
InvalidArgument - - Thrown if any parameter is null
